  "text": "The transition rate (4.25) is non-Planckian. A Planck spectrum is obtained either when the acceleration a is about equal to the detector's frequency ω or in the regime of small accelerations a ≪ ω. In this regimes, however, we have demonstrated that the non-Markovian effects are really significant, rendering the transition rate non-thermal [CITATION_1] .",
